27.04	Bitmap_index	Bitmap index	On the left, identifier refers to the unique number assigned to each customer, gender is the data to be indexed, the content of the bitmap index is shown as two columns under the heading bitmaps. Each column in the above illustration is a bitmap in the bitmap index. In this case, there are two such bitmaps, one for gender Female and one for gender Male. It is easy to see that each bit in bitmap M shows whether a particular row refers to a male. This is the simplest form of bitmap index. Most columns will have more distinct values. For example, the sales amount is likely to have a much larger number of distinct values. Variations on the bitmap index can effectively index this data as well. We briefly review three such variations.	
